Citation.sTitle: Excess Molar Volumes and Viscosity Deviations of Binary Mixtures of 2,4,6-Trimethyl-1,3,5-trioxane + Ethanol, 1-Propanol, and 1-Butanol at (298.15, 303.15, and 308.15) K
Citation.sAbstract: Densities and viscosities of binary mixtures of 2,4,6-trimethyl-1,3,5-trioxane + ethanol, 1-propanol, and 1-butanol have been measured at (298.15, 303.15, and 308.15) K. From these measurements, excess molar volumes (VE) and viscosity deviations (ae) were calculated. These results were fitted to the Redlich- Kister polynomial. The results were discussed in terms of molecular interactions.
